            <biogHist>
                <p>Angus MacNiven was first recorded in 1841 at 20 years old and living with his
                    mother Ann MacNiven in Balindore, Muckairn. On 23 March 1849 he married Ann
                    McIntyre of Glencruten, Kilbride and they had 7 children: Dugald, Mary, Christy,
                    Donald, Margaret, Anne and Angus. In 1861 the census recorded an apprentice
                    tailor, John Paterson, living with the family. In 1865 Angus married Mary
                    McCallum and had 6 children: Dugald, James, John, Catherine, Archie and Jessie.
                    Angus died in September 1900 and the cause of death recorded as cardiac failure
                    resulting from infirmity of age.</p>
                <p>Carmichael recorded a story entitled 'Burns' from MacNiven on 25 July 1892. </p>
